COARDS, CF-1.6, ACDD-1.3, NCCSV-1.0: Seawater Measurements\nSea Surface Temperature and Salinity:\nSea Surface Temperature (SST) in degrees C is from the ship\u2019s Hull Probe (SBT38, calibrated on Sep. 17, 2019), Salinity in PSU is from the ship's SeaBird  thermosalinograph (SBE 45, calibrated on Sep. 25, 2019). The temperature probe and water inlet for the thermosalinograph were located 5.3 meters below the water line. The underway chlorophyll data are from the ship\u2019s Seapoint fluorometer, which was calibrated by the factory on Nov. 21, 2019.
